We applied the K-means clustering method as proposed in out previous work [19] to identify non-responder participants. This unsupervised approach offers an objective alternative to heuristic, threshold-based criteria. The input data consisted of session-wise MI accuracy values from all TG and PG participants, yielding one accuracy vector per participant. Clustering was performed with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
