				\begin{document}$$k = 2$$\end{document}, aiming to separate responders from non-responders. It was hypothesized that non-responders within the TG would display MI performance profiles more closely aligned with those of the PG group (who are not expected to successfully learn to self-regulate their brain activity), and would thus be classified within the cluster primarily comprising PG participants.

